{"type":"message","id":"177dd579","parentId":"f4940b73","timestamp":"2026-03-24T18:22:24.236Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_koazo1iv5tck_2","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 142114\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/STRATEGY_C_HYBRID_EXPERIMENT.md (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the most impactful next action.\r\n\r\nFrom the goals document, I can see:\r\n\r\n1. **Phase 0 COMPLETE**: Sandbox foundation established\r\n2. **Phase 1 COMPLETE**: Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec synthesized\r\n3. **CFI Compression Experiment COMPLETE**: Key finding is that we need a hybrid approach\r\n\r\n**Pending Action from the session insights:**\r\n- **Hybrid CFIA-Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)** - This is the most concrete next step\r\n- Formula: score(T) = CFI(T) A- min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n- Test: distinguish \"constant format\" from \"research trajectory\"\r\n- Run: 200 pulses, 80/20 split, compare against binary thresholds\r\n\r\nThe synthesis document `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md` exists and documents the full experiment. The next logical step is to implement and run the Hybrid scoring experiment.\r\n\r\nI need to create an experiment script that:\r\n1. Implements the hybrid scoring formula\r\n2. Runs on 200 pulses with 80/20 split\r\n3. Compares against binary thresholds\r\n4. Documents results\r\n\r\nLet me look at what files exist and what would be most impactful to edit or create.\r\n\r\nLooking at the existing structure, I should probably:\r\n1. Create a new experiment script for the hybrid scoring\r\n2. Or update the CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md with the experiment plan\r\n3. Or create a new experiment directory/file\r\n\r\nThe most impactful action would be to create the experiment script for Strategy C (Hybrid CFIA-Freq scoring). This directly follows from the insights about the three-dimensional filter and the pending experiment.\r\n\r\nLet me create a new experiment script or update the existing research document with the experiment design.\r\n\r\nActually, looking at this more carefully - the next concrete action should be implementing and running the hybrid scoring experiment. I should create a script or update the research document with the experiment plan and begin executing it.\r\n\r\n\r\nI'll focus on creating a new experiment file to test the hybrid scoring approach. The goal is to design a systematic way to distinguish between constant format and research trajectory tokens. I'll draft a comprehensive experiment script that incorporates the scoring formula and defines clear evaluation metrics.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI compression experiment revealed that binary thresholds fail because constant-format tokens (freq�%^160, CFI=1) look causal but carry zero information. The hybrid scoring formula is ready but not yet tested.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate experiment script for Strategy C (Hybrid CFIA-Freq scoring) to test whether `score(T) = CFI(T) A- min(1, freq(T)/120)` distinguishes constant-format from research trajectory tokens.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Strategy C: Hybrid CFIA-Freq Scoring Experiment\r\n**Created:** 2026-03-24\r\n**Status:** READY TO RUN\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nThe formula `score(T) = CFI(T) A- min(1, freq(T)/120)` will:\r\n- Penalize constant-format tokens (freq=160, CFI=1.0 �+' score=1.0 A- 1.0 = 1.0 �?O FAILS)\r\n- Pass research trajectory tokens (freq=80, CFI=0.8 �+' score=0.8 A- 0.67 = 0.53 �o\")\r\n- Pass rare significant tokens (freq=5, CFI=0.9 �+' score=0.9 A- 0.042 = 0.038 �o\")\r\n\r\n**Problem:** Score=1.0 for constant format - this formula alone doesn't distinguish!\r\n\r\n## Revised Formula\r\n`score(T) = CFI(T) A- sqrt(min(1, freq(T)/120))`\r\n\r\n- Constant (freq=160, CFI=1.0): score = 1.0 A- �^s1.0 = 1.0 (unchanged - need ADDITIONAL filter)\r\n- Research (freq=80, CFI=0.8): score = 0.8 A- �^s0.67 = 0.8 A- 0.82 = 0.65\r\n- Rare (freq=5, CFI=0.9): score = 0.9 A- �^s0.042 = 0.9 A- 0.20 = 0.18\r\n\r\n## Three-Dimensional Filter (FINAL)\r\n```\r\nINCLUDE(T) iff:\r\n  CFI(T) >= 0.5  AND\r\n  freq(T) >= 3   AND\r\n  freq(T) < 120\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis explicitly EXCLUDES:\r\n- Constant format: freq=160 �%� 120 �+' EXCLUDED\r\n- Rare noise: freq<3 �+' EXCLUDED\r\n- High CFI but wrong frequency band �+' EXCLUDED\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n- **Dataset:** 200 pulses (use existing pulse corpus)\r\n- **Split:** 80% train (160 pulses) / 20% test (40 pulses)\r\n- **Baseline:** Binary thresholds from Strategy A/B\r\n- **Metric:** Precision, Recall, F1 on \"meaningful tokens\"\r\n\r\n## TODO\r\n- [ ] Implement three-dimensional filter\r\n- [ ] Run on 200 pulses\r\n- [ ] Compare against baselines\r\n- [ ] Update CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md\r\nfile: research/STRATEGY_C_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 14:21:34"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1121,"aggregated":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 142114\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/STRATEGY_C_HYBRID_EXPERIMENT.md (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the most impactful next action.\r\n\r\nFrom the goals document, I can see:\r\n\r\n1. **Phase 0 COMPLETE**: Sandbox foundation established\r\n2. **Phase 1 COMPLETE**: Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec synthesized\r\n3. **CFI Compression Experiment COMPLETE**: Key finding is that we need a hybrid approach\r\n\r\n**Pending Action from the session insights:**\r\n- **Hybrid CFIA-Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)** - This is the most concrete next step\r\n- Formula: score(T) = CFI(T) A- min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n- Test: distinguish \"constant format\" from \"research trajectory\"\r\n- Run: 200 pulses, 80/20 split, compare again